⭐ DOCUMENT 2 — Copyright Clarification Announcement
Title:
How Copyright Works — What Creators Should Know

Body:
Copyright protection is automatic the moment you create something. You do not need to file, register, or publish anything for your work to be protected. Copyright gives you exclusive rights to reproduce, distribute, display, and adapt your work.

However, proving authorship and timeline can be difficult without clear evidence. The IP Continuity Watermark Standard and the public vault help creators establish visible, timestamped records that support authorship claims. These tools do not replace copyright law; they strengthen your ability to demonstrate when your work existed.

Copyright protects your rights.
Continuity helps you prove them.
